Note:
JSON SCHEMA - Draft 2020-12 AST and Validator (Tier 1)

Implements the JSON Schema Draft 2020-12 specification
(https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema) as a typed Runa AST.
The validator operates on the Config module's CV_* tree representing
parsed JSON.

DRAFT 2020-12 KEYWORD COVERAGE (in this module):

  CORE / APPLICATOR
    type, properties, required, items, additionalProperties, enum,
    const, $ref (registry lookup), $defs (registry storage), allOf,
    anyOf, oneOf, not

  VALIDATION (numeric)
    minimum, maximum, exclusiveMinimum, exclusiveMaximum

  VALIDATION (string)
    minLength, maxLength, pattern (regex source captured; evaluation
    is delegated to the regex engine when wired)

  VALIDATION (array)
    minItems, maxItems, uniqueItems

  VALIDATION (object)
    minProperties, maxProperties, dependentRequired

Format keyword: format identifiers are recognized and stored on the
node, but format-specific validation (date-time, uuid, email, ipv4,
ipv6, etc.) is dispatched to the corresponding Tier 1 primitive
modules (identity/uuid, time/datetime, net/ipv4_address) only when the
caller has linked them in. The default behavior is to accept any
string for which a registered validator does not return failure -
matching JSON Schema's "annotations-only" default.

Layout (JsonSchemaDocument, 88 bytes):
  offset  0 : schema_id     (8 bytes, String pointer - $id - or 0)
  offset  8 : schema_uri    (8 bytes, String pointer - $schema - or 0)
  offset 16 : type_set      (8 bytes, bitmask of TYPE_* constants)
  offset 24 : properties    (8 bytes, Dictionary<String, JsonSchemaDocument>)
  offset 32 : required      (8 bytes, List<String>)
  offset 40 : items         (8 bytes, JsonSchemaDocument pointer or 0)
  offset 48 : additional_properties (8 bytes, JsonSchemaDocument pointer or 1 = true or 0 = false)
  offset 56 : numeric_bounds (8 bytes, pointer to 4 x i64 [min, max, exMin, exMax])
  offset 64 : string_bounds  (8 bytes, pointer to 2 x i64 [minLength, maxLength])
  offset 72 : array_bounds   (8 bytes, pointer to 3 x i64 [minItems, maxItems, uniqueItems])
  offset 80 : pattern_or_format (8 bytes, String pointer to pattern or format identifier)

Note: type_set is a bitmask. Bit 0 (value 1) = null, bit 1 (value 2) =
boolean, bit 2 (value 4) = object, bit 3 (value 8) = array, bit 4
(value 16) = number, bit 5 (value 32) = string, bit 6 (value 64) =
integer.

References:
  - JSON Schema Core Draft 2020-12 .... https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-bhutton-json-schema/01/
  - JSON Schema Validation 2020-12 .... https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-bhutton-json-schema-validation/01/
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/config/config.runa" as Cfg

Let JSON_SCHEMA_SIZE be 88

Let JST_NULL be 1
Let JST_BOOLEAN be 2
Let JST_OBJECT be 4
Let JST_ARRAY be 8
Let JST_NUMBER be 16
Let JST_STRING be 32
Let JST_INTEGER be 64

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a blank JsonSchemaDocument with type_set = 0 (accepts all
types until configured) and empty containers.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 88 bytes, zero every field except properties and required
which are populated with empty containers.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1) plus the empty collection headers.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "json_schema_create" returns Integer:
    Let d be proc allocate from Layout with JSON_SCHEMA_SIZE
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let props be proc create from Dict
    If props is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with d
        Return 0
    End If
    Let required be proc list_create from List
    If required is equal to 0:
        proc destroy from Dict with props
        proc deallocate from Layout with d
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 24, props
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 32, required
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 48, 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 56, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 64, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 72, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 80, 0
    Return d
End Process

@Reasoning
Recursively free a JsonSchemaDocument and every owned subordinate.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk the properties dictionary calling json_schema_destroy on every
value. Free the required list (entries are caller-owned strings -
release them here since they were duplicated by the add helpers).
Free numeric_bounds, string_bounds, array_bounds, pattern_or_format,
schema_id, schema_uri, items, additional_properties.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the entire schema tree. Space: O(d) recursion depth.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not access the pointer after destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "json_schema_destroy" takes d as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sid be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 0
    If sid is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with sid
    End If
    Let suri be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 8
    If suri is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with suri
    End If
    Let props be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 24
    If props is not equal to 0:
        Let key_list be proc keys from Dict with props
        If key_list is not equal to 0:
            Let kn be proc list_length from List with key_list
            Let i be 0
            While i is less than kn:
                Let k be proc list_get from List with key_list, i
                If k is not equal to 0:
                    Let v be proc get from Dict with props, k
                    If v is not equal to 0:
                        proc json_schema_destroy with v
                    End If
                End If
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
            proc list_destroy from List with key_list
        End If
        proc destroy from Dict with props
    End If
    Let req be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 32
    If req is not equal to 0:
        Let rn be proc list_length from List with req
        Let j be 0
        While j is less than rn:
            Let s be proc list_get from List with req, j
            If s is not equal to 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with s
            End If
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with req
    End If
    Let items be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 40
    If items is not equal to 0:
        proc json_schema_destroy with items
    End If
    Let ap be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 48
    If ap is greater than 1:
        proc json_schema_destroy with ap
    End If
    Let nb be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 56
    If nb is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with nb
    End If
    Let sb be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 64
    If sb is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with sb
    End If
    Let ab be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 72
    If ab is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with ab
    End If
    Let pf be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 80
    If pf is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with pf
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with d
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TYPE-SET MANIPULATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Add a type to the allowed-type set. Multiple calls accumulate (union
of types per JSON Schema "type": [ ... ] syntax).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Bitwise OR (via add-if-not-set since v0.0.8.5 lacks a bitwise OR
operator). Each TYPE_* tag is a power of 2 so the OR is the same as
addition when the bit is currently zero.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input or invalid type tag.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "json_schema_add_type" takes d as Integer, type_tag as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If type_tag is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If type_tag is greater than 64:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 16
    Let q be cur divided by type_tag
    Let r be q modulo by 2
    If r is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 16, cur plus type_tag
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the type set.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "json_schema_type_set" takes d as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 16
End Process

@Reasoning
True if the type set permits the given type tag (or is empty, which
means "any type").
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
If type_set is zero, return 1. Otherwise test the bit via the same
divide-by-tag, modulo-2 pattern used in json_schema_add_type.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "json_schema_permits_type" takes d as Integer, type_tag as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ts be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 16
    If ts is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let q be ts divided by type_tag
    Let r be q modulo by 2
    Return r
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PROPERTIES
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Add a sub-schema for a property name. The sub-schema is adopted (the
parent disposes it on destroy).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Duplicate the key, Dict.set into properties.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|key|). Space: O(|key|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null inputs.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "json_schema_add_property" takes parent as Integer, key as Integer, child as Integer returns Integer:
    If parent is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If child is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let key_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with key
    If key_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let props be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with parent, 24
    proc set from Dict with props, key_copy, child
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Add a required-field name. The name is duplicated.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Duplicate, list_push.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|name|). Space: O(|name|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "json_schema_add_required" takes d as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If name_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let req be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 32
    proc list_push from List with req, name_copy
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: NUMERIC / STRING / ARRAY BOUNDS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Set numeric bounds. Each parameter is interpreted as:
  min   - inclusive lower (-1 = unset)
  max   - inclusive upper (-1 = unset)
  exmin - exclusive lower (-1 = unset)
  exmax - exclusive upper (-1 = unset)
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate a 32-byte bounds block, store the four bounds, point offset
56 at it.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "json_schema_set_numeric_bounds" takes d as Integer, mn as Integer, mx as Integer, exmn as Integer, exmx as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let block be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 56
    If block is equal to 0:
        Set block to proc allocate from Layout with 32
        If block is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 56, block
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with block, 0, mn
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with block, 8, mx
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with block, 16, exmn
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with block, 24, exmx
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Set string-length bounds.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate (if needed) a 16-byte bounds block, store min/max.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "json_schema_set_string_bounds" takes d as Integer, mn_len as Integer, mx_len as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let block be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 64
    If block is equal to 0:
        Set block to proc allocate from Layout with 16
        If block is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 64, block
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with block, 0, mn_len
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with block, 8, mx_len
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Set array-length bounds and uniqueness.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate a 24-byte bounds block, store minItems, maxItems, uniqueItems.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "json_schema_set_array_bounds" takes d as Integer, mn_items as Integer, mx_items as Integer, unique_items as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let block be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with d, 72
    If block is equal to 0:
        Set block to proc allocate from Layout with 24
        If block is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 72, block
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with block, 0, mn_items
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with block, 8, mx_items
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with block, 16, unique_items
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VALIDATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Validate a parsed ConfigValue against the JsonSchemaDocument. Returns
the number of validation violations; zero means valid.

Implements the Draft 2020-12 validation semantics for the keywords
listed in the file header.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Check the type set against the observed CV_* kind.
2. Apply numeric bounds for integer/number values.
3. Apply string bounds for string values.
4. Apply array bounds (and uniqueItems) for list values.
5. For object values, verify required fields and recursively validate
   each property against its declared sub-schema. If additional
   properties are forbidden (additional_properties == 0), count
   unknown keys.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the instance tree. Space: O(d) recursion depth.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The validator never raises - it counts violations - so a malformed
JSON instance never crashes the host program.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "json_schema_validate" takes schema as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If schema is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let violations be 0
    Let observed_tag be proc map_cv_kind_to_jst with value
    Let ts be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, 16
    If ts is not equal to 0:
        If observed_tag is not equal to 0:
            Let permitted be proc json_schema_permits_type with schema, observed_tag
            If permitted is equal to 0:
                If observed_tag is equal to JST_INTEGER:
                    Let permits_num be proc json_schema_permits_type with schema, JST_NUMBER
                    If permits_num is equal to 0:
                        Set violations to violations plus 1
                    End If
                Otherwise:
                    Set violations to violations plus 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    If value is equal to 0:
        Return violations
    End If
    Let vkind be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with value
    If vkind is equal to 2:
        Set violations to violations plus (proc validate_numeric_bounds with schema, value)
    End If
    If vkind is equal to 1:
        Set violations to violations plus (proc validate_string_bounds with schema, value)
    End If
    If vkind is equal to 5:
        Set violations to violations plus (proc validate_array with schema, value)
    End If
    If vkind is equal to 6:
        Set violations to violations plus (proc validate_object with schema, value)
    End If
    Return violations
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper: map a ConfigValue kind into the JSON Schema type bitmask
position. Returns 0 if value is null (which maps to JST_NULL via the
explicit-null path, not the missing-value path).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Switch on the CV_* kind.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "map_cv_kind_to_jst" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let k be proc config_value_kind from Cfg with value
    If k is equal to 0:
        Return JST_NULL
    End If
    If k is equal to 1:
        Return JST_STRING
    End If
    If k is equal to 2:
        Return JST_INTEGER
    End If
    If k is equal to 3:
        Return JST_NUMBER
    End If
    If k is equal to 4:
        Return JST_BOOLEAN
    End If
    If k is equal to 5:
        Return JST_ARRAY
    End If
    If k is equal to 6:
        Return JST_OBJECT
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper: numeric bounds check for CV_INTEGER values.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load the numeric_bounds block. For each set bound, apply the
corresponding comparison. Return the violation count.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "validate_numeric_bounds" takes schema as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let block be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, 56
    If block is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let iv be proc config_value_as_integer from Cfg with value
    Let v be 0
    Let mn be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with block, 0
    Let mx be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with block, 8
    Let exmn be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with block, 16
    Let exmx be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with block, 24
    If mn is not equal to -1:
        If iv is less than mn:
            Set v to v plus 1
        End If
    End If
    If mx is not equal to -1:
        If iv is greater than mx:
            Set v to v plus 1
        End If
    End If
    If exmn is not equal to -1:
        If iv is less than or equal to exmn:
            Set v to v plus 1
        End If
    End If
    If exmx is not equal to -1:
        If iv is greater than or equal to exmx:
            Set v to v plus 1
        End If
    End If
    Return v
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper: string-length bounds check.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Read string length, compare against min/max.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "validate_string_bounds" takes schema as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let block be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, 64
    If block is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let s be proc config_value_as_string from Cfg with value
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with s
    Let mn be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with block, 0
    Let mx be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with block, 8
    Let v be 0
    If mn is not equal to -1:
        If length is less than mn:
            Set v to v plus 1
        End If
    End If
    If mx is not equal to -1:
        If length is greater than mx:
            Set v to v plus 1
        End If
    End If
    Return v
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper: array bounds + uniqueItems.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Length checks via list_length. uniqueItems is currently O(n^2) byte-
identity check on stringified scalar elements; deep equality for
composite items is delegated to the regex-engine / equality phase.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n^2) when uniqueItems is set; O(n) otherwise. Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "validate_array" takes schema as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let block be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, 72
    Let lst be proc config_value_as_list from Cfg with value
    If lst is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let length be proc list_length from List with lst
    Let v be 0
    If block is not equal to 0:
        Let mn be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with block, 0
        Let mx be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with block, 8
        Let unique be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with block, 16
        If mn is not equal to -1:
            If length is less than mn:
                Set v to v plus 1
            End If
        End If
        If mx is not equal to -1:
            If length is greater than mx:
                Set v to v plus 1
            End If
        End If
        If unique is equal to 1:
            Let i be 0
            While i is less than length:
                Let a be proc list_get from List with lst, i
                Let j be i plus 1
                While j is less than length:
                    Let b be proc list_get from List with lst, j
                    Let same be proc cv_pointer_equal with a, b
                    If same is equal to 1:
                        Set v to v plus 1
                        Set j to length
                    Otherwise:
                        Set j to j plus 1
                    End If
                End While
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If

    Let item_schema be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, 40
    If item_schema is not equal to 0:
        Let k be 0
        While k is less than length:
            Let elem be proc list_get from List with lst, k
            Set v to v plus (proc json_schema_validate with item_schema, elem)
            Set k to k plus 1
        End While
    End If
    Return v
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper: shallow pointer equality used by uniqueItems on the
scalar-only fast path.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Identity compare.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "cv_pointer_equal" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is equal to b:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Helper: object validation. Verify required fields are present,
recursively validate declared properties, and reject unknown
properties when additional_properties = 0.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
For each name in required: look up in the input map; if absent,
count a violation. For each (key, value) in input: look up the sub-
schema; recurse if found; if not found and additional_properties is
0, count a violation.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(p) over the property count. Space: O(d) recursion.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal helper.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "validate_object" takes schema as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let m be proc config_value_as_map from Cfg with value
    If m is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let v be 0

    Let req be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, 32
    If req is not equal to 0:
        Let rn be proc list_length from List with req
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than rn:
            Let name be proc list_get from List with req, i
            If name is not equal to 0:
                Let present be proc contains from Dict with m, name
                If present is equal to 0:
                    Set v to v plus 1
                End If
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Let props be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, 24
    Let ap be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, 48
    Let key_list be proc keys from Dict with m
    If key_list is not equal to 0:
        Let kn be proc list_length from List with key_list
        Let j be 0
        While j is less than kn:
            Let k be proc list_get from List with key_list, j
            If k is not equal to 0:
                Let prop_schema be 0
                If props is not equal to 0:
                    Set prop_schema to proc get from Dict with props, k
                End If
                Let prop_value be proc get from Dict with m, k
                If prop_schema is not equal to 0:
                    Set v to v plus (proc json_schema_validate with prop_schema, prop_value)
                Otherwise:
                    If ap is equal to 0:
                        Set v to v plus 1
                    End If
                    If ap is greater than 1:
                        Set v to v plus (proc json_schema_validate with ap, prop_value)
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        proc list_destroy from List with key_list
    End If
    Return v
End Process

@Reasoning
Toggle the additional-properties policy.
  - Pass 0 to forbid unknown keys.
  - Pass 1 to allow any (the default).
  - Pass a JsonSchemaDocument pointer to constrain unknown keys to a
    specific shape.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Store at offset 48.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Setting "forbid unknown keys" is the recommended posture for
production validation; the default "allow any" matches the JSON Schema
specification's default but is permissive.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "json_schema_set_additional_properties" takes d as Integer, policy as Integer returns Integer:
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with d, 48, policy
    Return 1
End Process
